This paper is primarily focused on face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The proposed method involves the use of a novel loss function to improve the performance on hard samples, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of state-of-the-art classifiers and benchmarks, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography (cs.CR).
